1. Phishing email attacks, where fraudsters send malicious emails pretending to be from a reputable company or person, requesting personal information; 
2. Malware attacks, where fraudsters embed malicious software on vulnerable websites and steal users' information as they enter it; 
3. Social engineering tactics , like disguising as a official-looking government representative to elicit personal information over the phone; 
4. Imitating well-known trusted companies by creating deceptively similar websites;
5. Pretexting , where fraudsters create convincing but false stories about an individual in order to obtain their personal details; 
6. SMS and voice phishing attacks that use texts or voices to coerce people into revealing sensitive data.
